# User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
The UAT is conducted to evaluate the usability and effectiveness of our RamenDesk Software.
Potential users such as students and lecturers were let to experience the prototype and provide feedback on the software based on the navigation, functionality, and the overall experience.
The UAT was conducted by using Google Form to collect users’ feedback after they tested our prototype. 

## Overall findings 
Both students and lecturers responses were mainly positive and they enjoyed using RamenDesk as they found it helpful in completing their daily tasks.
For instance, students favourite feature was the interactice quiz as it involves gamification elements whihc keeps them motivated to practice their learning.
For lecturers, their favourite was the lecturer consultation booking as it facilitates them in communicating with students systemtically in terms of booking consultation time.
